[h4 id=DifficultyLevel 
	" Difficulty level
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"In the past, we generally preferred movies done on the hardest difficulty provided that they demonstrate the best superhuman gameplay with some exceptions where lower difficulty allowed even better demonstration of the game. This is no longer the case as it's now up to the author to decide on what difficulty fits their goal, such as the easiest difficulty for a purely speed oriented movie or the default difficulty to best demonstrate a score oriented goal.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=NES River City Ransom|href=/4344M)
		", the easier difficulty is used as it mostly affects how often enemies and bosses block. Less blocking means less of a need to manipulate the actions of the AI.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=GBC Pong: The Next Level|href=/4912M)
		", the fastest difficulty setting is Medium as this allows for faster paddle movement compared to Easy difficulty but doesn't upgrade the opponent AI compared to Hard difficulty.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Rockman no Constancy|href=/5415M)
		", the Hard mode patch introduces a weapon energy bug that results in reducing the need to refill the ammo for Item 1 compared to the Normal mode patch. While the other changes result in Hard mode being slower the weapon energy bug introduces new strategies that the Normal mode can't use.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In movies whose goal is "maximum score", such as 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Aero Fighters|href=/5802M)
		" and 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Shienryu|href=/6013M)
		", the default arcade difficulty is used. This is done to properly compare real time arcade high score records which are generally done on default factory settings.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"In some games, you can access some extra items, stages, bosses and/or achieve some hidden endings if you are on a certain difficulty, which is usually but not always the hardest one. Having this happening might interfere with your decided movie goals. There are also cases where the content between difficulties is different enough in how to approach and optimize for that there can be publications of each difficulty level. So make sure that you have investigated the secrets in the game.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" In the Japanese version of 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Ranger X|href=/769G)
		", there's an Easy difficulty exclusive stage that's not playable on harder difficulties. However, the Easy difficulty requires entering an in-game code to access.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=NES Double Dragon II|href=/2481M)
		", the only way to access all the stages as well as the game's ending is to finish the game on the hardest difficulty.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Gunstar Heroes|href=/3274M)
		", The Seven Force boss's phases is determined by the difficulty level, with all 7 only available on Hard difficulty and higher.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" In 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Monkey Ball Jr.|href=/854G)
		", each difficulty has their own distinct set of stages to clear. While the general mechanical strategies would apply to both difficulties, the 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Beginner stages|href=/5841M)
		" require their own routing challenges compared to the 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Master stages|href=/2924M)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 id=AutoSave 
	" Auto-save
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
